        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:18AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 318 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
north of Horntown, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Raiford...                        Hanna...
Indianola...                      Vernon...

This includes Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 241 and
245.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern, northeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
